 Port Elizabeth - All communities being serviced by the Kabega Park police station are advised that this police station is temporarily closed due to a police officer having tested positive for the Covid-19 virus. "Part of the Community Service Centre will be operating from the satellite station at Rocklands – response attendance and serious crime dockets opened at the satellite station,' said police spokesperson, Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo. "The other part of the CSC will be operating from the SAPS Information Desk at the Baywest Shopping Centre – Affidavits, accident reports and permit applications will be done during the day and at Rocklands in the evening." Brig Naidoo said that the station’s contact details will be temporarily suspended however contact to Rocklands satellite station is 041 9555710 and to the Information Desk at Baywest, Col Tony Nomdoe on 082 303 0504 "The station will be decontaminated and the community will be informed when the station will be re-opening," he added. "SAPS management apologises for any inconvenience that may arise from this." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 